AUDIO: 'For years, I\'ve refused to better myself as a web developer by getting really good at design and tools like Figma. Well, yesterday that decision finally started to pay off because Google just murdered Figma by announcing a massive update to their vibe design tool, Stitch. If you\'ve never heard of it,'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it\'s an infinite canvas tool that allows you to easily generate designs for your UI UX needs like web pages and app screens. Designer Gary Simon is literally shaking right now. If you are UI UX designer, you are living in the'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dark ages. Because you don\'t need to start with a wireframe anymore. You just start with a vibe. You tell it what your product should feel like, who it\'s for, maybe throw in a screenshot or a URL of a design you want to steal, or maybe'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just whisper into your mic like a lunatic. Then it simply summons the devil straight from the hexagon of Saturn to build a UI for you like magic. But here\'s the crazy part. It doesn\'t stop at static designs. Stitch can instantly turn those into interactive'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prototypes and simulate full user flows with a single click. The tool just got an upgraded new slot renderer, but the best new feature is actually a humble little design.md markdown file that could completely change your app'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'development workflow. In today\'s video, we\'ll take a look at everything new in Google Stitch and find out if it\'s just more hype or a true game-changer for untalented designers. It is March 19th, 2026 and you are watching The Code Report. I\'ve been failing to build a'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'good UIs for nearly two decades now. I still remember my very first website, which took weeks of painstaking CSS work in Adobe Dreamweaver. Luckily though, many years later design implementation got way easier thanks to tools like'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Tailwind CSS. But sadly, now AI tools like Stitch are killing the CSS tooling business. A couple months ago, Tailwind had to lay off most of its team. And honestly, it makes sense because Tailwind was never really about design,'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it was about making implementation faster. As a free and open source tool, they tried to monetize the business by selling premium templates. But in 2026, nobody buys premium templates anymore. Why memorize utility classes like flex,'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'BG blue dash 500, gap four, and so on when instead you can just say build me a clean SAS dashboard with good spacing and modern typography? And because of that reality, despite being more popular than ever, Tailwind is now surviving on'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'donations like a homeless person. And check this out. I really like the design system used on the fireship.dev website, which was created by a real human named Lynn with real talent. But because I\'m lazy, I can now just feed Google Stitch'

[02:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a website URL and it will instantly build me a design system that I can now use in any project. And stealing is awesome because now I can put this design system to work on my billion-dollar app idea, HorseTender. I tell Stitch to build a homepage and it\'s'

[02:34] [scene:talk]
